Data Modeling¶

In [29]:
all_data = []

for i in range(len(data)):
    image = cv2.imread(data['path'][i])
    image = cv2.resize(image, (50, 50)) / 255.0
    label = 1 if data['corona_result'][i] == "Positive" else 0
    all_data.append([image, label])
In [33]:
x = []
y = []

for image, label in all_data:
    x.append(image)
    y.append(label)

# Converting to Numpy Array    
x = np.array(x)
y = np.array(y)

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 0)
x_train, x_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(x_train, y_train, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 0)

print(x_train.shape, x_test.shape, x_val.shape, y_train.shape, y_test.shape, y_val.shape)

Convolutional Neural Network¶

In [34]:
cnn_model = models.Sequential()

# First convolutional layer
cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(50, 50, 3)))
cnn_model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))
cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.3))

# Second convolutional layer
cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
cnn_model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))
cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.5))

# Third convolutional layer
cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))

# Flatten layer to transition from convolutional to dense layers
cnn_model.add(layers.Flatten())

# Dense layers
cnn_model.add(layers.Dense(units=16, activation='relu'))
cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.2))

# Output layer
cnn_model.add(layers.Dense(units=2))

# Model summary
cnn_model.summary()

In [85]:
def evaluation_parametrics(name, y_train, yp_train, y_val, yp_val, y_test, yp_test):
    
    print("\n-----------------------------{}-----------------------------\n".format(name))
    
    cm_train = confusion_matrix(y_train, yp_train)
    t1 = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(cm_train)
    s1 = round((cm_train[0,0]/(cm_train[0,0] + cm_train[0,1])),4)
    
    print("Classification Report for Train Data\n")
    print(classification_report(y_train, yp_train)) 
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    print("Recall on Train Data: ", round(recall_score(y_train, yp_train),4))
    print("Specificity on Train Data: ", s1)
    print("Accuracy on Train Data: ", round(accuracy_score(y_train, yp_train),4))
    print("Precision on Train Data: ", round(precision_score(y_train, yp_train,zero_division=0),4))
    print("F1 Score on Train Data: ", round(f1_score(y_train, yp_train),4))
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    
    t1.plot()
    plt.show()

    cm_val = confusion_matrix(y_val, yp_val)
    t2 = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(cm_val)
    s2 = round((cm_val[0,0]/(cm_val[0,0] + cm_val[0,1])),4)
    
    print("\nClassification Report for Validation Data\n")
    print(classification_report(y_val, yp_val))   
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    print("Recall on Val Data: ", round(recall_score(y_val, yp_val),4))
    print("Specificity on Val Data: ", s2)
    print("Accuracy on Val Data: ", round(accuracy_score(y_val, yp_val),4))
    print("Precision on Val Data: ", round(precision_score(y_val, yp_val,zero_division=0),4))
    print("F1 Score on Val Data: ", round(f1_score(y_val, yp_val),4))
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")

    t2.plot()
    plt.show()


    cm_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, yp_test)
    t3 = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(cm_test)
    s3 = round((cm_test[0,0]/(cm_test[0,0] + cm_test[0,1])),4)
    
    print("\nClassification Report for Test Data\n")
    print(classification_report(y_test, yp_test))   
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    print("Recall on Test Data: ", round(recall_score(y_test, yp_test), 4))
    print("Specificity on Test Data: ", s3)
    print("Accuracy on Test Data: ", round(accuracy_score(y_test, yp_test), 4))
    print("Precision on Test Data: ", round(precision_score(y_test, yp_test,zero_division=0), 4))
    print("F1 Score Test Data: ", round(f1_score(y_test, yp_test), 4))
    print("--------------------------------------------------------------------------")
     
    t3.plot()
    plt.show()

from tensorflow import keras

data_augmentation = keras.Sequential([
    preprocessing.Rescaling(1./255, input_shape=(50, 50, 3)),
    layers.RandomFlip("horizontal"),
    layers.RandomRotation(0.1),
    layers.RandomZoom(0.2),
])

augmented_cnn_model = models.Sequential()

# Add the image augmentation layer as the first layer

# First convolutional layer
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.3))

# Second convolutional layer
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.5))

# Third convolutional layer
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))

# Flatten layer to transition from convolutional to dense layers
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Flatten())

# Dense layers
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Dense(units=16, activation='relu'))
augmented_cnn_model.add(layers.Dropout(0.2))

Using Pre-Trained Model (VGG16)¶

In [68]:
# Resize the images to (224, 224, 3)
x_train_resized = tf.image.resize(x_train, (224, 224))
x_val_resized = tf.image.resize(x_val, (224, 224))

base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

# Freeze the convolutional layers
for layer in base_model.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

# Create a new model on top of the VGG16 base
model = models.Sequential([
    base_model,
    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dropout(0.5),
    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')  
])

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history = model.fit(x_train_resized, y_train, epochs=10, validation_data=(x_val_resized, y_val))
